    "description": {
      "value": "<p><strong>Source</strong> <em>Armor Master's Handbook pg. 28</em></p><p><strong>Aura</strong> moderate transmutation <strong>CL</strong> 10th</p><p><strong>Slot</strong> armor quality; <strong>Price</strong> +15,000 gp; <strong>Weight</strong> -</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><img src=\"modules/pf-content/assets/PathfinderSocietySymbol.gif\" title=\"PFS Legal\" style=\"margin:3px 3px 0px 3px;\"><strong>Description</strong></h3>On command, the wearer of a suit of <em>radiant flight</em> armor can conjure a pair of batlike wings from her back that shed light like a torch. These wings grant a fly speed of 30 (poor maneuverability) for 10 minutes per day. This duration need not be used consecutively, but must be used in 1-minute increments. The <em>radiant flight</em> special ability can be applied only to heavy armor.</p><p><h3 class=\"framing\"><strong>Construction</strong></h3><strong>Requirements</strong> Craft Magic Arms and Armor, <em>fly</em>; <strong>Price</strong> 7,500 gp</p>",
